@copilot dont put crypto on globalThis. Nothing should be made global. It looks like crypto is only used for uuid generation. You can just put this implementation in the code base as a utility 

```javascript 
function uuid() {
  let d = new Date().getTime();

  return 'xxxxxxxx-xxxx-4xxx-yxxx-xxxxxxxxxxxx'.replace(/[xy]/g, function(c) {
    const r = (d + Math.random() * 16) % 16 | 0;
    d = Math.floor(d / 16);
    return (c === 'x' ? r : (r & 0x3 | 0x8)).toString(16);
  });
}

// Usage:
console.log(uuid());
```

